This paper is about deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on policy gradient methods, which are commonly used in reinforcement learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also deals with control variate methods, which are commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses deep neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV).
